
Tcl command: cb_talk [ options ]
Type: object
C++ class: cb_talk
Description: This is the CBserver object.

    Options:
	-answerformat <the format of the answer from ask> (default FRAME)

	-errorhandler <the Tcl command that is called if an error occurs> (default )

	-rollback <the rollback time for the query of an ask command> (default Now)

	-answerformat <> (default the format of the answer from ask)

	-errorhandler <> (default the Tcl command that is called if an error occurs)

	-rollback <> (default the rollback time for the query of an ask command)


    Methods:
	connect connect_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp, int argc, char** argv)
                Connects server, usage: <object> connect port host client\n                [user]
	disconnect disconnect_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                Disconnects server
	getErrorMsg getErrorMsg(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                delivers an internal errormessage
	tell tell_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* telos)
                tells some telos-frames to the CBserver
	untell untell_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* telos)
                untells some telos-frames to the CBserver
	ask ask_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp, int argc, char** argv)
                asks the CBserver, usage: <object> ask answerVar query\n                [format]
	send_message send_message_CB(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* method, char* date)
                sends a message to the CBserver (hardcore), usage: <object>\n                send_message <method> <date>
	lastCompletion lastCompletion(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the  last completion value of connect, tell, ask,\n                ...
	lastPort lastPort(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last port of a connect-call
	lastHostname lastHostname(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last hostname of a connect-call
	lastClientname lastClientname(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last clientname of a connect-call
	lastUsername lastUsername(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last username of a connect-call
	lastAnswerobject lastAnswerobject(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last answer, which was stored to an answervariable\n                by the ask command
	lastAnswer lastAnswer(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last answer of ask
	lastAnswerformat lastAnswerformat(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last used answerformat
	lastQuery lastQuery(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last used query
	lastErrormessage lastErrormessage(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the last errormessage
	lastAnswertime lastAnswertime(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the time of last response time 
	sessionAnswertime sessionAnswertime(Tcl_Interp* interp)
                returns the summary response time 
	resetAnswer resetAnswer(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* newAnswer)
                resets the intern value of lastAnswer, note that this function\n                is only for the purpose of errorhandling
	resetAnswerobject resetAnswerobject(Tcl_Interp* interp, char* newAnswerobject)
                resets the intern value of lastAnswerobject, note that this\n                function is only for the purpose of errorhandling
